I couldn_t breathe. There was just too much happening all at once. It seemed like voices were surrounding all of me. Making it difficult to breathe. Difficult to function. I couldn_t help the thousand thoughts running through my mind. Making breathing harder by each second. It was like the world has come crashing down and I was the only one to witness it. Everyone around me was the same but I was different. And hell  even the thought causes another one of these episodes. For there was always that small nagging thought at the back of my mind making it impossible to be at peace. I was smiling but I wasn_t happy. It was all a faade. It was a time-ticking bomb and slightest movement would make it burst. It was like a volcano waiting to erupt. I was nothing and everything all at once. I was afraid to do anything due to the fear that the bomb would go off. Destroying me once again. Leaving me as nothing. Having to build myself back up every day. This was anxiety at its finest. 3 am and I_m awake because I just think how everyone from hs must look at me at shop n save and laugh amongst themselves at how I got fat again  and how I work a shitty job at a grocery store. I_m awake thinking of how many people see me post about mental health and say  good she deserves it . I am thinking of the fact that I_m a pathetic creature not worth the title of human that should probably actually die. I think how this won_t get the views and likes of my other pictures. It_s 3 am and this is my mental illness. My mental illness keeps me awake scouring the internet to reassure myself that everyone is better off without me. That everyone that I have left or that have left me are better off. From the drifting apart to the once we met eyes bc we shared a class in hs. Not having a facebook helps  it isn_t as easy. I realize no one checks on me like I do them. No one cares. And that makes everything worse. Like the people who are there aren_t good enough. They should be but not in this broken fucked mind. They all smile in their pictures. Look at my fucking page. It would be so easy at 3am. So easy. But instead I make an insta post I_ll delete and try to force my brain to move on from this destructive path. I always say  no one better acted surprised when I off myself. EMOTIONS  Today I embrace every single emotion that runs through my entire multi dimensional being. ................. I spent the majority of my life (my old life before complete transformation) hiding and running from all of the feels because I didn_t know how to be with them. I was constantly frightened  riddled with anxiety and deep rooted depressions and allowing repeated experiences into my reality. This was my normal  I spent years emotional eating  taking drugs to self medicate and numb myself  drinking and basically on a constant road to self destruct. .............. Today my normal is feeling all the feels with complete love  understanding  compassion  non-judgement and complete nurture for myself. I enjoy my being and my life that I have created while recognising my journey to get here and feeling complete gratitude. I love and value my life instead of constantly feeling like I wanted to end it. ................ Constantly hearing as a child negative words  witnessing self destructive behaviours and hearing that life is hard and life isn_t fair leaves you growing up believing theses words and then maps out your entire life. ................ We need to be kind and nurture ourselves as adults  undo what has stood in our path to experiencing joy and allow our children to really bring forth the wisdom they are born with. Give them a chance and you will see how amazing they are. .................... Stop trying to control them just to appease your own inner turmoil and fear of being judged by others. Not only do you suffer as a parent but your child does. .................... Life is good  life is joyful  life is full of love. You just need to be able to see it. Take the time to do the inner work and allow a new perspective to come through  I offer 1 to 1 mentoring to women and mothers. After reading news about the love island contestant Sophie Gradon taking her own life  it again highlights that depression or mental illness doesn_t look a particular way and that those who are truly suffering often hide it so well. It doesn_t matter how beautiful  rich  popular or happy people may appear on the surface and in particular on social media now a days it doesn_t mean they are not suffering inside and just because someone has the biggest smile doesn_t mean that it isn_t hiding a world of pain. Looking at Sophies profile only a few days ago she looked so happy and like she has it all  just goes to show how wrong that can be. Those that need help often look like those don_t and so this is a shout out to all my beautiful friends  family  or people I know that you are not and never alone and that if you ever need anything I_m here  even if I don_t see you all the time don_t ever be afraid to reach out to me or others around you. If you ever need anything I will always be here  I will never judge you or think less of you  I love you all!!! Anyone suffering with mental health out there just to let you know you are beautiful  you are loved and you are worth it! Keep fighting! . . I wish the stigma surround mental health didn_t play such a role in preventing people from reaching out and getting the help they require! It_s ok not to be ok and in a world where there are so many pressures from such things as social media  we need to support each other more and be there for one another and recognise the increase in depression especially in the younger generation now and not bury our heads in the sand! Run (The Good Omen) This is a warm up doodle before a commision piece im about to work on. Ive had this sudden idea  that needed to get out. Im about to get a little ranty here  if you want to stop reading from this part  no hard feelings  i promise. Depression and Anxiety! Alot of people have it. Alot of handle it differently. Thats fine. This is about mine  hopefully someone will read this who feels the same as i do and this may bring them some sort of good feelings  if its just one person  then this post and these words are worth something. I hate talking about it. But its something that i want to talk about in this piece. Life fucking sucks sometimes. Alot. Sometimes it piles up and you just gotta suffer through  cause maybe something good may happen at the end or not. Who knows Thinking about this makes me hope something good will come at the end of all this  that ill get out of this rut of mudane shit and i wont be left alone with these thoughts and feelings throughout my head. That  hey  ya know  pushing through all this shit was worth it. For now. I have my art. Its been sorta bringing me down. Its like  right now  my brain and hand arent working together right  right now. This piece is a sketch to warm up to get them working back together. Its a Jackalope on the run. From what Well  thats up to you. Arts up for interpretation. Ive been doing alot of jackalope pieces recently  and i decided to look up what jackalopes are supposed to mean. Good Omen and Good Fortune. Now  that could be wrong. But thats what im going to think of from now on whenever i think of a jackalope. I hope that whoever reads this decides to look at jackalopes in this light as well. I hope that when you see this  youll know in your head to keep running towards your good omen. Run towards your bliss  ya_ll. It is finally Friday! Getting up from bed was a real challenge today ! I literally had to force myself to do that. Some days just start like that. I have to  reanimate  myself in the morning - coffee shot  cold water to wash my face. But I did that and I am ready to start my day if work.  I started suffering from morning wakefulness again. We feel very tired in the morning. But we have to be tough like a samurai. Combat your apathy  lack of motivation and fatigue with a sword of your strong will. It is your superpower! My top 10 suggestions for the Millennial generation to apply: 1. Save money from every paycheck you receive by sacrificing all unnecessary spendings. 2. Pay off all debts asap. Interest rates will weigh heavy on your long term income. 3. Learn new skills independently versus the university model in order to create new ideas of services  products  and art while avoiding the currently overpriced educational system. 4. Take care of your health by consuming whole foods to ensure your wellness. Being sick costs time and money. 5. Avoid eating out  partying  spending on entertainment and clothes at retail price. The  minimalist  lifestyle. 6. Sell any and everything you don_t need. Doesn_t hurt to clear up space at home while making some extra cash. 7. Barter your independent services to friends  neighbors  and community. It_s vital these days to be skilled in something outside of your regular job. 8. Start an online business. Your product and services can reach customers outside your town and can go as far as worldwide. 9. Invest wisely. Doesn_t have to be the stock market  but it can also be on food storage  artwork  whatever you believe will be worth something more in the future. 10. Keep up with the trends! This world is moving so fast that we must constantly pay attention to know what the next  big thing  is going to be. Imagine if we knew that Google  Amazon  Facebook  Apple  etc were going to be worth what they are today... I pray these suggestions offer solution and spark the light that many of us need. The past month has brought forth a whole new phase or level or season (whatever you want to call it) of grief. It has sucked. I have thought about making a video about it  but my strength isn_t quite there yet on this topic. In short though...I_m suffering from some form of PTSD. My current struggles stem from 4 major losses over the course of this past year. Jake  a family member  and 2 miscarriages. And the truth is that in this  season  of grief  my mind goes daily to places of the absolute worst things that could happen now. It_s like if I can already take my mind there and realize that it could happen  that it will somehow prepare me for if it ever does. I can_t even begin to describe to you how dark and debilitating this can be (unless you_ve been through it too). I hate typing that out. I hate that this is where I_m at on some days now. It is real life though. And as I_ve felt God nudge and push me totally out of my comfort zone on many days throughout this journey of healing and restoration  I can say this is another area that He said let me use you. And not by your strength Allyson  but Mine.  . .  So today_s devotional (from my newest daily devo book  Jesus Always  by Sarah Young my sweet Mama gave me on Sunday after I got to speak to the ladies at my church) reminded me that I would not be trapped in this grief and this sadness forever. And it_s wild to say that y_all because I DO HAVE JOY!

Friends I cannot begin to tell you how important this is in our lives. // G O O D . N E W S // Do you need to hear some good news  There was a study about the effects of OULA that was finished up earlier this year and it had awesome results!!! Basically  it showed that OULA can boost happiness  and lower depression and anxiety! How cool is that!! Here is a little more information about the study:  From November 2016  January 2018  Dr. Tracy Hellem and colleagues conducted a study that evaluated OULA as an intervention for women with moderate levels of depression. Women attended OULA at least once per week for 12 weeks  and then abstained from OULA for one week. Depression  anxiety  and happiness were measured weekly. They found that over the course of the 12 weeks there was a trend in reduced depression and anxiety and increased happiness. When women abstained for OULA after the 12 weeks  an increase in depression and anxiety was noted (see charts below). The researchers concluded that OULA is a reasonable option to improve depression and anxiety  although further studies will be conducted to better understand the relationship between OULA and depression and anxiety.  So remember  when you feel stressed  depressed  anxious  or just need a little happiness in your heart  hop into an OULA class  hug a fellow OULAkin if you need to  and leave feeling just a little lighter  oulafitness modernmindbodyfitness happyheart mentalhealth depression anxiety happiness effectsofoula feelgood research socool

Grateful Friday....Where do I even start this week I just experienced a bucket list trip for so many people this past week. While I never really imagined myself going to Alaska  I am beyond blessed that I was able to experience all the beauty there. Alaska is pure  down to earth  jaw dropping gorgeous with such unique and beautiful wildlife. The best part of the trip though was spending time with my sister  Katy. We laughed so hard and really just continued to strengthen and deepen our bond. She has supported and encouraged me for my entire life and is my number one cheerleader. The trip was physically and mentally challenging  and I know I was able to keep up and do all the things we did due to my training with DNRS. I am beyond grateful to have a toolbox to get me through any situation. I was able to eat all foods/drinks with no reactions. I was able to move more than I normally do with little pain. I was able to function on less sleep than I typically get at home  and experience no chronic fatigue. I still have work to do  and am beyond appreciative to have a network of individuals who are also going through the program who I can call on at any time or night for help and support.  Now  I get to experience another adventure with my husband to an amazing resort in Asheville  NC. I am fortunate to be able to live a laptop/smartphone lifestyle where I can work from anywhere. NoOffice. This to me is the true freedom in life. What are you grateful for this week I_d love you to share with me. I_ve learned that we can be grateful for the smallest things  and there is so much beauty in that. My days were spent clinging to my good friend depression  My nights weren_t any better. My disordered mind thought I was living life right   You_ll never make it  they would say  so stay with me . That_s exactly what I did. I slept and ate abnormally. My mind swimming with fears  and anxieties. The thought of school made me sick to my stomach  and mum thought I was faking. The nights were a fine line between death and life. Every night I walked a tight rope  and every night I was afraid I would full. Some nights I slept for hours  Others I would stay up till 4am. Looking up at the sky in wonder. Wondering why I was placed on this earth if all I ever thought about was death or skinny. It wasn_t a life I was living. I wasn_t alive  but I was still living  and nothing hurt more than to scream  my lungs filling with water but nobody could hear me. My mind consumed with what could of been. I seem to be the family disappointment. My sister always said I was the pretty one  But I would take smart over pretty any day. My mum constantly asking what was wrong with me  made me think something was wrong with myself. My dad speaking  but I couldn_t hear a thing. Tears flowing down my face  Was I the only one who could see them Why was I crying Life was perfect. I should of been happy. Why wasn_t I happy My mind. School. Bed. School. Bed. Tear drops became my only friend. Depression robbed me of my teenage years. Suicidal thoughts took me from my friends. Anxiety stole me from my family. Words I couldn_t speak. I became mute. At sixteen I was just a lifeless body faking a smile. At eighteen I talked only when I had to. Nineteen things started looking up  but only for a while. Twenty  I took a breath of death. Twenty one  life is good. I_m happy. I help people like me. I found veganism. I have created this platform of lovely souls. My days are consumed with hand holds  and cuddles from the patients I work with. The sun is out in my mind. I find joy in collecting flowers.reading books. And hearing others life stories.i cuddle my dog more. I laugh more. I say  I love you more . And if there was anything I would tell my teenage self  it truly does get better.i promise.
